1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
A checkout can look finished and still stop a keyboard user cold.
AccessPatch EU turns that failure into an evidence-backed patch.

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Five Tab presses return focus to Email. The payment control is unnamed,
and the visible validation error is silent to assistive technology.

3
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Playwright and axe-core capture a privacy-scrubbed keyboard trace,
DOM, accessibility evidence, screenshot, and source hints.

4
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Three stable findings connect runtime behavior to source:
AP-EU-001, AP-EU-002, and AP-EU-003.

5
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:31,000
GPT-5.6 correlates bounded browser evidence with React source
and proposes the smallest repair. Deterministic tests decide pass/fail.

6
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Nothing is edited yet. A human must explicitly approve,
and the editable root remains src/checkout.

7
00:01:48,000 --> 00:02:08,000
The approved diff changes only the evidence-backed behavior,
then AccessPatch scans again and replays the same keyboard journey.

8
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:26,000
The known blockers resolve, no new critical axe finding appears,
and keyboard checkout reaches order confirmation.

9
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Built with Codex and GPT-5.6. The signed-in local workflow needs no
OpenAI Platform API key and provides evidence, not certification.
